cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about image segmentation using convolutional neural networks, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a method to add spatial regularization to CNNs, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to improve model performance and robustness. The paper also mentions the use of total variation (TV), which is a mathematical concept commonly used in optimization problems (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on several datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
